6
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:50,120
[Second Shot at Love]

7
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:09,980
[Prevention and Treatment of Alcoholism]

8
00:01:11,190 --> 00:01:14,680
Korea is very tolerant toward alcohol.

9
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:17,240
You can easily purchase alcohol
at any time of day.

10
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:20,240
You can drink anywhere.

11
00:01:21,340 --> 00:01:22,880
[Who is an alcoholic?]

12
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:29,000
Which one is an alcoholic?

13
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,610
You might think it's the homeless man,

14
00:01:31,610 --> 00:01:34,770
who is too drunk to even walk.

15
00:01:38,510 --> 00:01:41,010
But that's not necessarily the case.

16
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,010
<i>It may also be people</i>
[Han Geum Ju / Senior Engineer]

17
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:05,430
<i>who have enviable jobs, and</i>

18
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:09,120
are seen as hard-working experts in their fields.

19
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,310
An alcohol abuse diagnosis

20
00:02:11,310 --> 00:02:14,400
is not about societal status
or professional competency.

21
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,610
<i>Cheers.</i>

22
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:20,580
<i>If you're losing the ability to control
how much you drink,</i>

23
00:02:20,580 --> 00:02:22,570
you might...

24
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:27,330
[Ju Yeop]

25
00:02:27,330 --> 00:02:29,090
[15 Missed Calls from Ju Yeop]

26
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:33,310
already be an alcoholic.

27
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:38,560
Must be crazy.

28
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,200
She's drunk.

29
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:26,750
[Episode 1: A Very Rational Alcoholic]

30
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:35,930
When did you get here?

31
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,460
You weren't picking up my calls.

32
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:43,030
Do you know how many times I called?

33
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,930
I didn't know.

34
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:48,530
I was grabbing a drink with Mi Yeon.

35
00:03:52,270 --> 00:03:53,840
Geum Ju.

36
00:03:58,230 --> 00:04:00,450
Do you love booze that much?

37
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,300
Let me ask you something.

38
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:06,420
Alcohol or me. Which do you choose?

39
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,680
Alcohol.

40
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:12,990
- What?
- I prefer booze to you.

41
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:26,890
Let's forget about getting married.

42
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:40,330
Oh, Ju Yeop.

43
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:44,060
Oh, no. Here I go again.

44
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:47,600
Son-in-law, it's still lunch hour, right?

45
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:51,460
I brought some rice cakes for you
to share with your co-workers...

46
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:57,860
What?

47
00:04:58,730 --> 00:05:01,070
What do you mean?

48
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,710
What?

49
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:19,360
Seven, seven, seven...

50
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:38,420
Wait... What is this...

51
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:40,220
Geum Ju.

52
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,690
Han Geum Ju!

53
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,080
Wait...

54
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:47,050
Where did she go after making this mess?

55
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,200
Geum Ju...

56
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,580
Gosh...

57
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,410
Hey, Han Geum Ju.

58
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,860
Get up right now!

59
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:08,830
Mom!

60
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,060
How could you ambush me like this without warning?

61
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,250
Without warning, my foot.

62
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:14,990
You wanted to shop for furniture
for your newlywed home.

63
00:06:14,990 --> 00:06:16,380
You said to pick out a fridge
and a washing machine.

64
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:19,260
I told you so many times I was coming today!

65
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:24,500
Speaking of, how could you ambush me like this?

66
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,100
Ju Yeop told me everything.

67
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:28,960
You told him you prefer alcohol to him?

68
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,620
You called off the engagement?

69
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:33,830
That blabbermouth. He wasted
no time ratting me out.

70
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,490
Aigoo.

71
00:06:35,490 --> 00:06:37,520
It must be true, then.

72
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:42,410
Hey. Are you insane?

73
00:06:42,410 --> 00:06:45,120
Drinking is a normal part of social life.

74
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,590
How can I marry a man who doesn't understand that?

75
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:48,910
What did you just say?

76
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:52,130
He loved my drinking when we were dating.

77
00:06:52,130 --> 00:06:54,620
But he totally changed once we set the date.

78
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:57,700
He nags me every single day.

79
00:06:57,700 --> 00:06:59,490
How can I live my whole life with a man like him?

80
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:00,950
Absolutely not.

81
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:04,110
Marriage is not a joke.

82
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:05,950
Go beg at his feet.

83
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,680
Tell him you'll quit drinking.

84
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:11,020
Leave it. Why would I quit drinking for him?

85
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:14,400
I'm not the kind of woman
who lives and dies for a man.

86
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:17,500
I must've slept in a weird position...

87
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,890
Aigoo...

88
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:21,980
Are you okay?

89
00:07:23,030 --> 00:07:24,290
You think I'm okay?

90
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:26,390
You think I'm okay right now?

91
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:34,380
[Ad: Contact me if you need to borrow money fast]

92
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:35,940
Geez.

93
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:47,020
<i>Ju Yeop, I'll make Geum Ju beg at your feet.</i>

94
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:49,290
<i>Please come to her apartment.</i>

95
00:07:49,290 --> 00:07:51,090
He did read the text,

96
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:54,380
but no reply. And he won't pick up his phone.

97
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:56,350
Aigoo, what am I supposed to do?

98
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:58,400
What do I do?

99
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,120
He must be here. Aigoo!

100
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,130
You're here, Ju Yeop.

101
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,500
A bonus item!

102
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,550
What are you doing right now?

103
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:14,450
You haven't eaten anything all day.

104
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:17,230
I ordered chicken stew with neungi mushroom.

105
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,660
You want me to eat the stew now?

106
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:20,440
When you deserve to be stewed alive?

107
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,450
Come on. Stop.

108
00:08:22,450 --> 00:08:23,910
Stop what?

109
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:26,430
Ju Yeop won't pick up my calls now.
What will you do?

110
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:29,240
Gosh, stop calling.

111
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,740
I'm not getting married.

112
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,580
That's it? You won't get married?

113
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,260
Marriage is not like a pension reservation.

114
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:36,130
You think you can back out by changing your mind?

115
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:38,190
You can cancel a one-night stay at a pension.

116
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:39,520
Marriage is for the rest of your life.

117
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,960
You should cancel it if you're not feeling it.

118
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,440
You think you're all that?

119
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,160
Marriage or whatever,

120
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:47,120
I'm just going to focus on my work now.

121
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,460
Focus on your work?

122
00:08:48,460 --> 00:08:50,600
I thought you got extended leave
for ten years of service.

123
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,910
Focus on work, my foot.

124
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:54,040
I asked to be reinstated.

125
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,020
[HR]

126
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:58,610
Speak of the devil, this is work.

127
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:08,430
<i>Gosh, I'm sorry. It turned out that way.</i>

128
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:12,770
<i>The groom's mother was such a diva.</i>

129
00:09:12,770 --> 00:09:16,650
I could tell this marriage would
bring a lot of hardship.

130
00:09:16,650 --> 00:09:18,650
So, I suggested they break it up.

131
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:22,430
I'll treat you to a meal sometime. Okay.

132
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:24,030
Must you do all that?

133
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,670
Then, should I say that my daughter

134
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,710
broke it off because she prefers alcohol?

135
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:29,850
Aren't you embarrassed of yourself?

136
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:31,360
Why would I be embarrassed?

137
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,720
Shut up.

138
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,780
I'm the one who called off this wedding.

139
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,990
You keep your mouth shut.

140
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:37,530
So, why did you have to drag me

141
00:09:37,530 --> 00:09:39,670
all the way down here?

142
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:42,380
Why? Why?

143
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:46,000
Speak of the devil, this is work.

144
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,110
"Senior Engineer Han Geum Ju.

145
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:50,890
We regret to inform you that
reinstatement will not be possible

146
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:52,760
as a replacement has been hired during

147
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:55,270
your requested extended leave..."

148
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:58,050
"Reinstatement will not be possible"?

149
00:09:58,050 --> 00:09:59,430
Aigoo.

150
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:01,870
Your marriage fell apart,
your reinstatement fell apart...

151
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:03,900
And your apartment lease ends this month.

152
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:05,640
You already put the newlywed home on the market.

153
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:07,600
The one you put the deposit and savings on.

154
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,670
Am I supposed to just leave you stranded?

155
00:10:09,670 --> 00:10:10,770
Why would I be stranded?

156
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:13,300
I can just stay at student dorms
until the house sells.

157
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:14,570
Shut up.

158
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:16,110
Quit drinking, no excuses.

159
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,200
Become a new person and go back.

160
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,880
I have no intention of quitting drinking.

161
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:23,140
Oh, I see. Then, quit being my daughter.

162
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:26,100
Let's quit being mother and daughter.

163
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,730
What are you doing?

164
00:10:58,730 --> 00:11:00,070
Go!

165
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:01,770
Fine...

166
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,600
All right...

167
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:21,050
Wow, I don't think I need to come anymore.

168
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:23,600
Really? Am I healed?

169
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,240
No. Not at all.

170
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,560
You haven't healed a bit.

171
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,070
You've gotten worse.

172
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,420
So, why won't you come anymore?

173
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:40,220
What's the point of me coming
all this way to see you?

174
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:42,140
You don't take your medicine.

175
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,110
And I bear the brunt.

176
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:46,900
I won't treat a patient who won't listen. I won't.

177
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:49,340
I'm sorry. I forgot.

178
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:51,570
I've been busy working in the fields.

179
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:54,630
Pardon? I told you to rest, and you worked?

180
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,860
Wow, this is too much.

181
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:58,090
- Head nurse.
- Yes.

182
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:00,140
I won't be coming here anymore.

183
00:12:00,140 --> 00:12:01,950
I hope you live a long life.

184
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:04,890
Gosh, why did you do that?

185
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,510
What do you mean?

186
00:12:06,510 --> 00:12:09,120
It's harvest. Everyone's busy helping each other.

187
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:11,420
I can't just slip out.

188
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:15,350
Unless someone were to take my place...

189
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:17,880
Doctor.

190
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,190
Me?

191
00:12:22,190 --> 00:12:24,130
No way.

192
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:27,600
Doctor Seo, you're back.

193
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,820
You are!

194
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:31,600
You took my place last time.

195
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,340
And you're here instead
of Grandma Soon Ae this time.

196
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:36,550
Gosh, you're so sweet.

197
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:39,840
It's not an easy thing to help someone like this.

198
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:43,190
I'm helping myself, not someone else.

199
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:45,340
What do you mean?

200
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:47,430
If a sick person gets sicker while working,

201
00:12:47,430 --> 00:12:48,680
they'll call me over,

202
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,120
and that means I need to travel all this way.

203
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,640
I am helping myself

204
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,930
because I don't want to go through that.

205
00:12:54,930 --> 00:12:56,090
Okay, okay.

206
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:59,640
We got you. Why don't we take a break?

207
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,330
While we take a break,

208
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:04,040
what if the Doctor sings a song for us?

209
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,000
Love it!

210
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,870
Come on. The work is hard enough.

211
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:08,960
No way I'll sing.

212
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,310
Just one song.

213
00:13:11,310 --> 00:13:13,000
Sing for us!

214
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,550
<i>Sing for us!</i>

215
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,720
<i>Sing for us!</i>

216
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:19,330
- Gosh, I said I won't.
- <i>Sing for us!</i>

217
00:13:19,330 --> 00:13:23,310
♫ <i>When rain pours</i> ♫

218
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:30,120
♫ <i>I will be the biggest umbrella
in the world for you</i> ♫

219
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:34,720
♫ <i>So you can walk in peace</i> ♫

220
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:40,320
♫ <i>If you grow tired on your walk</i> ♫

221
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,450
- Good?
- No way!

222
00:13:42,450 --> 00:13:45,020
You can't just end it there! Sing more!

223
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:46,640
Let's focus on work.

224
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,980
We need to harvest all the way to there today.

225
00:13:49,980 --> 00:13:52,330
Let's hurry up.

226
00:14:02,130 --> 00:14:03,890
Great work!

227
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:06,200
- You're amazing.
- Come again!

228
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,390
Come back.

229
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:11,360
Grandma Kim Jeong Ja has
severe rheumatoid arthritis.

230
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,770
I'm worried about her working in the field.

231
00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:15,980
Grandma Park Mal Soon's gastritis
is not getting better,

232
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,490
so I think we should switch the medication.

233
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,250
The osteoporosis for Grandma Lee Jeong Rae...

234
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:20,910
Stop.

235
00:14:21,710 --> 00:14:23,660
You just finished work.

236
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:25,420
Take a breather.

237
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:28,400
All right. Breathe in.

238
00:14:29,350 --> 00:14:31,170
Breathe out.

239
00:14:32,230 --> 00:14:34,150
Good job.

240
00:14:35,730 --> 00:14:39,300
I got these precious gifts, thanks to you.

241
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,650
How nice.

242
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:43,020
You're so good at field work.

243
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:47,430
I used to help out
when I lived with my grandmother.

244
00:14:47,430 --> 00:14:49,000
Oh, right.

245
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,920
You mentioned your grandmother's from here, Bochun.

246
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:53,380
Yes.

247
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:55,700
It's beautiful here.

248
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:59,000
It's healing just to look around.

249
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,820
So happy. Right?

250
00:15:07,390 --> 00:15:09,410
[Welcome to Lake Bochun Pension]

251
00:15:14,530 --> 00:15:16,280
Hurry up.

252
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:19,520
I'm coming...

253
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,670
Dad, cheers!

254
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,160
Who's this?

255
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,370
My precious baby daughter!

256
00:15:39,370 --> 00:15:42,170
Oh, Dad. Long time no see. You, too, Unni.

257
00:15:42,170 --> 00:15:43,370
What are you doing here?

258
00:15:43,370 --> 00:15:44,910
Weren't you getting ready
for the wedding all week?

259
00:15:44,910 --> 00:15:46,930
Yeah, I didn't even call

260
00:15:46,930 --> 00:15:48,420
because I didn't want to bother you.

261
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:52,200
What are you doing? In bright daylight.

262
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,550
We cleaned up right after the guests left.

263
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:56,770
We just got started. Just a drink after work.

264
00:15:56,770 --> 00:15:58,980
I thought I'd just have one drink

265
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:00,450
before the twins came home from school.

266
00:16:00,450 --> 00:16:02,020
It's so delightfully breezy today.

267
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,750
Perfect for day-drinking.

268
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:07,110
Gosh, my baby daughter.
You have amazing food luck.

269
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:10,190
We made this plum wine last year, and it's amazing.

270
00:16:10,190 --> 00:16:12,240
A welcome drink.

271
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:15,140
- Come here.
- Come here.

272
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:18,940
Welcome drink, my foot.

273
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,630
This is all because of you.

274
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:34,650
It's all because of you!

275
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,760
<i>While everyone else fed their kids
black bean noodles.</i>

276
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:39,960
<i>you two fed her liquor</i>

277
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,210
<i>and set them on a track.</i>

278
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:43,100
<i>Cheers!</i>

279
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,150
[Liquor immediately upon graduation]

280
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,750
That's not all.

281
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:49,340
<i>You'd stay up all night to drink.</i>

282
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:50,560
<i>You showed them how to drink.</i>

283
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:51,670
[Valedictorian alcoholic]

284
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,590
<i>And you drilled into them</i>

285
00:16:53,590 --> 00:16:55,610
<i>that drinking is the most important thing</i>

286
00:16:55,610 --> 00:16:57,760
<i>once you start working.</i>

287
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:01,260
That's how she became addicted to alcohol!

288
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:04,210
What are you talking about?

289
00:17:04,210 --> 00:17:06,080
That girl.

290
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:09,540
She broke off the engagement for liquor.

291
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:11,250
What?

292
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:13,400
He broke up with her for drinking too much?

293
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,630
That bastard...

294
00:17:14,630 --> 00:17:16,670
No, not bastard. Bitch.

295
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:18,790
He didn't break it off. She did.

296
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:20,800
Your daughter broke it off

297
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:23,160
because he nags her about drinking too much.

298
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,690
<i>What?</i>

299
00:17:26,830 --> 00:17:28,360
Mark my words.

300
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:30,580
There will be no more alcohol in this house.

301
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:32,480
Put your life on the line

302
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,680
if you're going to drink.

303
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:37,310
I'll end you for good!

304
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:52,840
Honey.

305
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:56,120
I heard Geum Ju out,

306
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,770
and she does have a point.

307
00:17:57,770 --> 00:17:59,030
Get out.

308
00:17:59,030 --> 00:18:00,640
Should I?

309
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:07,930
I knew he'd be like that.

310
00:18:07,930 --> 00:18:10,670
I didn't like how he acted at his first visit.

311
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:13,270
Remember? We offered him a tiny bit of liquor,

312
00:18:13,270 --> 00:18:16,240
and he passed out in the living room.

313
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,850
Actually, I knew it then.

314
00:18:18,850 --> 00:18:21,690
He's not cut out to join our family.

315
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:24,110
I know, right?

316
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:26,660
Gosh, all this wasted plum wine...

317
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:27,710
You'll get hurt.

318
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:29,990
Leave it. I'll take care of it.

319
00:18:29,990 --> 00:18:31,450
Is Mom okay?

320
00:18:31,450 --> 00:18:33,960
She's fine. You know her temper.

321
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:36,330
She gets fired up, and then she calms down.

322
00:18:36,330 --> 00:18:38,850
She'll get over it. It's okay.

323
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:41,150
I'm sorry. Because of me...

324
00:18:41,150 --> 00:18:43,660
Shut it. Don't talk like that.

325
00:18:43,660 --> 00:18:46,780
He's right. How can you live with someone

326
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:49,030
who nags you for social drinking?

327
00:18:49,030 --> 00:18:51,570
Breaking it off was the right thing to do.

328
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,130
You understand me, Unni.

329
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:55,530
Of course I do.

330
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:59,080
Marriages break apart even
if you're crazy about each other.

331
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:00,090
Look at me.

332
00:19:00,090 --> 00:19:02,730
Calling the wedding off is way better
than getting divorced like me.

333
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:06,430
What? Getting divorced is nothing in today's world.

334
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:09,010
That's what I'm saying. Divorce means nothing.

335
00:19:09,010 --> 00:19:10,280
Calling off a wedding is no big deal.

336
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,610
I completely agree.

337
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:14,080
Breaking off an engagement isn't
even news these days.

338
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:16,590
- Right?
- Totally.

339
00:19:18,110 --> 00:19:19,750
<i>What? Called off the wedding?</i>

340
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,850
Out of the blue?

341
00:19:20,850 --> 00:19:22,260
Yeah.

342
00:19:22,260 --> 00:19:25,880
The mother-in-law was a major diva.

343
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,020
What is she like?

344
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:29,370
Gosh, I don't even want to talk about it.

345
00:19:29,370 --> 00:19:31,470
It was obvious the mother would
make her life miserable.

346
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:33,910
How was I supposed to marry her off?

347
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:35,550
So, I broke it off.

348
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,910
Good job.

349
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:39,430
Geum Ju is your precious daughter.

350
00:19:39,430 --> 00:19:42,150
And no one should have to suffer
under a mother-in-law.

351
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:43,320
You did the right thing.

352
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:45,250
What was she like?

353
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:47,330
I said I don't want to talk about it.

354
00:19:47,330 --> 00:19:49,720
I thought she'd torture her if she stayed in Seoul,

355
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:52,610
so I dragged her here with me
since she's on vacation.

356
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:54,060
Gosh, seriously.

357
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:57,480
What in the world did she do that
you called off the wedding?

358
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:00,670
Hyungnim*, come on. W-What did she do?
(Same as "unni" among women)

359
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:04,030
Huh? What is it? Spill it.

360
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:07,210
Gosh, why, why, why did you do that?

361
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:08,680
Tell us!

362
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,190
How did it happen?

363
00:20:10,190 --> 00:20:12,290
She's just like you!

364
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,650
She just won't stop arguing.

365
00:20:14,650 --> 00:20:16,700
I couldn't bear it! Happy?

366
00:20:18,540 --> 00:20:20,570
Why are you lashing out at me?

367
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:23,130
Wow, it's almost like

368
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:27,440
there's some other reason
the engagement broke off.

369
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:34,170
What do you mean I lashed out?

370
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:37,360
Young Woong's mom, you didn't make
your daily payment today.

371
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,780
Can I pay you tomorrow?

372
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:39,960
Again?

373
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:42,320
You've pulled this way too many times!

374
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:45,630
Hyungnim...

375
00:20:45,630 --> 00:20:47,870
Every other time, you let it slide.

376
00:20:47,870 --> 00:20:51,160
Why are you so sharp today?

377
00:20:52,530 --> 00:20:55,460
I don't know what you're talking about.

378
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:58,780
I was just wondering if she knows
how many times it's been.

379
00:20:58,780 --> 00:20:59,920
I don't know, either.

380
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,180
Let's not keep count.

381
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:03,500
That's what I meant.

382
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,800
You can pay tomorrow. Tomorrow.

383
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,100
Thank you, Hyungnim.

384
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:08,350
Sure.

385
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:11,550
Well, I...

386
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:14,650
I'd better get going.

387
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:17,430
See you all tomorrow.

388
00:21:17,430 --> 00:21:19,480
Suddenly?

389
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,020
- You're leaving?
- Hyungnim...

390
00:21:22,020 --> 00:21:24,820
You're still wearing our apron and bandana...

391
00:21:32,740 --> 00:21:34,660
[This is Mirae Studio]

392
00:21:36,810 --> 00:21:39,230
Pre-wedding video, my foot.

393
00:21:41,230 --> 00:21:42,970
<i>We're getting married!</i>

394
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:50,710
[Ju Yeop and Geum Ju are getting married]

395
00:22:00,410 --> 00:22:01,950
[We promise to live happily ever after]

396
00:22:07,380 --> 00:22:10,380
We were so cringey.

397
00:22:11,750 --> 00:22:13,720
<i>Auntie! Woo Ri and Na Rah are here!</i>

398
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:16,290
<i>Auntie! Auntie Geum Ju!</i>

399
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:18,260
<i>Auntie!</i>

400
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:20,560
Auntie, Auntie, Auntie!

401
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:21,790
We just got home.

402
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:23,450
Oh, yes, just a moment.

403
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:25,600
- How have you been? Did you miss me?
- How many?

404
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,920
We missed you!

405
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,620
So, so much!

406
00:22:28,620 --> 00:22:30,970
Did you? Auntie, too!

407
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:34,030
Auntie, let's play outside.

408
00:22:34,030 --> 00:22:36,000
I want to go to Bochun Lake
and ride the merry-go-round.

409
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,960
Shall we? Okay! Let's go.

410
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:41,770
<i>Giddy up!</i>

411
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:44,330
Auntie! Hi!

412
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:46,930
Auntie, I'm here!

413
00:22:46,930 --> 00:22:48,880
Auntie!

414
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:52,700
When did they get so big? Woo Ri and Na Rah...

415
00:22:54,660 --> 00:22:55,970
Hey, Yeong Rong.

416
00:22:55,970 --> 00:22:58,690
Unni, did you really break off
your engagement and come to Bochun?

417
00:22:58,690 --> 00:23:01,110
Just a second.

418
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,850
Yeah.

419
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:06,340
I broke off the engagement.

420
00:23:06,340 --> 00:23:08,600
<i>Why?</i>

421
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,930
Keep this to yourself.

422
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:13,220
He constantly nagged me about my drinking.

423
00:23:13,220 --> 00:23:15,510
He finally made me pick between him and alcohol.

424
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:17,860
<i>And? What did you say?</i>

425
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:19,200
What do you think?

426
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,930
Obviously, I picked alcohol.

427
00:23:20,930 --> 00:23:22,490
And I called off the wedding.

428
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:24,600
<i>What did you just say?</i>

429
00:23:32,890 --> 00:23:34,600
Are you happy now?

430
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:38,090
Are you happy now that you've told
everyone you're an alcoholic?

431
00:23:38,090 --> 00:23:39,910
Mom, what do you mean I'm an alcoholic?

432
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:41,730
I'm just an alcohol connoisseur.

433
00:23:41,730 --> 00:23:43,690
I should smack you in the mouth.

434
00:23:43,690 --> 00:23:45,460
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

435
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,050
I didn't mean for the word to get out.

436
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:48,610
She's wrong for eavesdropping.

437
00:23:48,610 --> 00:23:50,100
Stop blabbering!

438
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:52,090
I'd better sew up your mouth
so you can't drink anymore.

439
00:23:52,090 --> 00:23:54,910
What? Aigoo, connoisseur?

440
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:56,970
- Connoisseur, my foot.
- Come on!

441
00:23:56,970 --> 00:23:59,400
- Mom, calm down.
- Please stop.

442
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,600
This is her first vacation
in a long time. Let her rest!

443
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,020
Let me go!

444
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:05,820
Geum Ju, split! Split!

445
00:24:05,820 --> 00:24:07,640
Hey! Stop right there!

446
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,030
Seriously!

447
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:12,570
How did I end up in Bochun?

448
00:24:12,570 --> 00:24:13,680
So annoying...

449
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,880
Hey, Geum Ju. Is it true?

450
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,960
You really called off your wedding for liquor?

451
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,330
I heard it with my own ears.

452
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:22,020
Geum Ju, why do you live like that?

453
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:23,500
Let me live the way I want.

454
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:27,400
<i>Rumor spread like charcoal smoke in tiny Bochun.</i>

455
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,690
<i>Geum Ju, we've got drinks that are worth
calling off a wedding for.</i>

456
00:24:29,690 --> 00:24:31,610
Want a drink with a side of pollock?

457
00:24:31,610 --> 00:24:34,570
The pride of Bochun,
hailed as a genius since childhood.

458
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:37,470
What became of the daughter of Bochun?

459
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:38,470
So upsetting.

460
00:24:38,470 --> 00:24:40,240
I'm not your daughter.

461
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:43,760
<i>I was a tastier drinking snack than pollack.</i>

462
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:46,770
<i>Geum Ju did always like to drink a little.</i>

463
00:24:46,770 --> 00:24:48,290
A little?

464
00:24:48,290 --> 00:24:50,070
She likes it enough to call off her wedding.

465
00:24:50,070 --> 00:24:52,110
That tells you everything.

466
00:24:52,110 --> 00:24:53,200
I can hear everything.

467
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:56,960
<i>I became gossip that's easier
to peel than an onion.</i>

468
00:24:56,960 --> 00:25:00,610
Your aunt can't get married
because she loves to drink too much?

469
00:25:00,610 --> 00:25:02,410
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- Stop.

470
00:25:02,410 --> 00:25:04,240
Kids, look here.

471
00:25:06,770 --> 00:25:10,310
It's not that Auntie can't get married
because she likes drinking.

472
00:25:10,310 --> 00:25:13,800
It's that she's not getting married
because she prefers drinking.

473
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:16,010
There's a major difference.

474
00:25:16,010 --> 00:25:18,160
There's a clear distinction. Okay?

475
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:20,020
Good going.

476
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:22,870
Teaching kids great lessons, Han Geum Ju.

477
00:25:22,870 --> 00:25:25,980
Gosh, this country town is the same as always.

478
00:25:25,980 --> 00:25:28,080
How does a rumor spread so quickly?

479
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:30,050
Gi Beom's mother is Bochun's loudspeaker.

480
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:31,980
Let me through.

481
00:25:31,980 --> 00:25:34,100
She's a part of so many group chats.

482
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:35,700
If she tapped all of them,

483
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:38,250
that means every newborn in Bochun knows.

484
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:41,030
Gosh, why did she have to catch me?

485
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,830
What's so bad about calling off a wedding?

486
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:44,660
Why is everyone making such a fuss?

487
00:25:44,660 --> 00:25:46,070
It's not for calling off a wedding.

488
00:25:46,070 --> 00:25:48,410
It's you breaking it off for liquor.

489
00:25:48,410 --> 00:25:50,510
I mean, you know this.

490
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:52,660
I work in a very male-dominated industry.

491
00:25:52,660 --> 00:25:55,590
I, Han Geum Ju, tried so very hard to survive

492
00:25:55,590 --> 00:25:58,950
in a space where you can't build
relationships without liquor.

493
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:01,500
I thought of drinking occasions
as an extension of work.

494
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:05,080
And how am I supposed to marry a guy
who nags me about drinking?

495
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:06,620
Wow, excuses galore.

496
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:08,620
You always loved to drink.

497
00:26:08,620 --> 00:26:09,800
That's what I'm saying.

498
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:12,400
I'm lucky to get to work in a field that suits me.

499
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,590
If it were me, I would've cheered him on

500
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:17,760
with a hangover remedy, instead of nagging.

501
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:20,150
You think you're all that.

502
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:22,780
Still, you've dated for a while.

503
00:26:22,780 --> 00:26:25,100
How come you don't seem
to have any lingering feelings?

504
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:27,110
Lingering feelings? What's that?

505
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:29,700
Is that the name of a new berry wine?

506
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:34,760
By the way, what's taking him so long?

507
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,330
[Bochun Car Center]
Gosh, so stressful.

508
00:26:37,330 --> 00:26:39,940
Hey, how long are you going
to wrestle with the car?

509
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,660
Yeah. I'm disappointed.

510
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:44,100
Your friend is here for the first time in forever.

511
00:26:44,100 --> 00:26:47,360
I'm sorry. I promised I'd fix this by today.

512
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:49,500
They said it was a brake issue, so I fixed it

513
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:51,570
but it's still not working.

514
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:54,720
Look. The warning light is still on.

515
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:57,120
Gosh, so stressful.

516
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,990
Can I take a look?

517
00:26:58,990 --> 00:27:00,270
I'd be grateful if you did.

518
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:04,310
Gosh, looks like I'll be working in a skirt today.

519
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,070
Got it.

520
00:27:33,270 --> 00:27:35,240
- The light's gone now.
- Daebak.

521
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:37,780
I had no idea it'd be an electrical issue.

522
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:39,750
Han Geum Ju strikes again.

523
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:43,460
Here I am, back on the scene.

524
00:27:43,460 --> 00:27:45,780
I fixed it.

525
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:48,480
Got it.

526
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,260
Are you friends with the car owner?

527
00:27:50,260 --> 00:27:51,800
I'm friends with him, too.

528
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,420
This is Ui Jun's car.

529
00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:55,330
Ui Jun? Seo Ui Jun?

530
00:27:55,330 --> 00:27:58,750
You didn't know? Ui Jun works at the Bochun Clinic.

531
00:28:00,230 --> 00:28:01,740
Darn.

532
00:28:01,740 --> 00:28:03,460
It must be Seo Ui Jun that I saw.

533
00:28:03,460 --> 00:28:04,790
You met up with him?

534
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:06,280
We brushed by each other.

535
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,690
I thought I mistook someone for him.

536
00:28:08,690 --> 00:28:10,520
Why is he in Bochun right now?

537
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:13,200
We thought we saw wrong at first, too.

538
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:17,210
A hotshot doctor in Seoul came
to a countryside clinic.

539
00:28:17,210 --> 00:28:19,940
<i>There's a serious medical vacuum in small towns.</i>
[Bochun Clinic, 1 Year Ago]

540
00:28:19,940 --> 00:28:22,670
<i>The clinic had closed over a year ago.</i>

541
00:28:22,670 --> 00:28:25,140
<i>Then, Ui Jun arrived like a king.</i>

542
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:28,230
<i>The entire town broke out in a festival.</i>

543
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:30,290
<i>It was a bigger celebration than</i>

544
00:28:30,290 --> 00:28:31,990
<i>if ancestors returned from the afterlife.</i>

545
00:28:31,990 --> 00:28:33,380
<i>Anyway,</i>

546
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:36,080
<i>Ui Jun is considered Bochun's God.</i>

547
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:38,810
<i>The savior of the townspeople.</i>

548
00:28:38,810 --> 00:28:43,690
Someone came here with major fanfare, and...

549
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:45,080
What about me? What?

550
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:46,670
Aigoo...

551
00:28:47,710 --> 00:28:49,140
You think...

552
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,390
Seo Ui Jun heard about my news already?

553
00:28:52,390 --> 00:28:55,080
Why? Are you embarrassed?

554
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,630
Me?

555
00:28:57,470 --> 00:29:00,420
Me? Hilarious.

556
00:29:00,420 --> 00:29:02,720
Why would I be embarrassed?

557
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:05,260
What happened between you and Ui Jun, by the way?

558
00:29:05,260 --> 00:29:07,110
You used to be super close.

559
00:29:07,110 --> 00:29:09,300
By chance, did he...

560
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:12,150
- nag you about your drinking, too?
- Gosh!

561
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:14,150
I don't know. I don't want to talk about him.

562
00:29:14,150 --> 00:29:16,110
I'm leaving.

563
00:29:16,110 --> 00:29:18,420
Geum Ju, Ui Jun is on his way.
Say hi before you leave.

564
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:21,620
Are you crazy? Why would I?

565
00:29:21,620 --> 00:29:24,180
I also have a lot to do, you know.

566
00:29:25,170 --> 00:29:29,200
Why didn't anyone tell me Seo Ui Jun is in Bochun?

567
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,990
<i>It's because you throw a fit</i>

568
00:29:30,990 --> 00:29:33,780
<i>every time anyone brings him up.</i>

569
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,730
Whatever. I bought soybean stew ingredients.

570
00:29:36,730 --> 00:29:38,600
Don't worry. Bye.

571
00:29:50,390 --> 00:29:52,150
[Year 2007]

572
00:30:04,590 --> 00:30:06,470
Hey, transfer student.

573
00:30:07,590 --> 00:30:10,290
What are you doing? Get on.

574
00:30:10,290 --> 00:30:12,180
Can't you tell?

575
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:15,200
Gosh, let me see.

576
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:17,430
Leave it. Go your way.

577
00:30:18,590 --> 00:30:21,020
What if I don't?

578
00:30:21,020 --> 00:30:25,700
Hey, you mustn't have heard about me yet.

579
00:30:27,830 --> 00:30:29,470
Here we go.

580
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:31,350
Why do you carry...

581
00:30:31,350 --> 00:30:34,910
I'm the expert fixer in this town.

582
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:36,630
When I was little,

583
00:30:36,630 --> 00:30:40,010
there was a genius discovery show,
and I was a young mechanic-

584
00:30:40,010 --> 00:30:43,220
- You were on that show?
- Almost.

585
00:30:43,220 --> 00:30:45,320
But I grew up too quickly.

586
00:30:46,130 --> 00:30:47,920
- What?
- Hey, hang on.

587
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,550
This will only take three minutes.

588
00:30:49,550 --> 00:30:52,490
Imagine you're heating up
instant curry and waiting.

589
00:30:55,070 --> 00:30:56,880
You ungrateful bastard.

590
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:59,380
Why is he here?

591
00:31:00,350 --> 00:31:02,460
Whatever. I'll just not see him.

592
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:05,050
I'll just make sure we don't run into each other.

593
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:09,060
Thank you...

594
00:31:19,330 --> 00:31:21,150
Han Geum Ju?

595
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:28,390
Long time no see. It's good to see you.

596
00:31:28,390 --> 00:31:30,030
Good to see me?

597
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:33,290
I don't think that's the nature of our relationship.

598
00:31:34,210 --> 00:31:35,730
I heard the news about your wedding-

599
00:31:35,730 --> 00:31:37,300
Yeah, I called off my wedding.

600
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:40,500
Because I didn't like him nagging me
about my drinking. Happy?

601
00:31:42,220 --> 00:31:44,630
What are you talking about?

602
00:31:44,630 --> 00:31:47,330
What? You said you heard the news.

603
00:31:47,330 --> 00:31:50,150
I heard the news about your wedding recently.

604
00:31:50,150 --> 00:31:52,270
I was about to congratulate you.

605
00:31:52,270 --> 00:31:54,830
But you broke off your engagement?

606
00:31:54,830 --> 00:31:56,590
Because of liquor?

607
00:31:56,590 --> 00:31:58,000
Yeah.

608
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:01,170
But the nature of our relationship isn't one where

609
00:32:01,170 --> 00:32:03,610
we make small talk and ask about personal matters.

610
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:05,260
I didn't ask you anything.

611
00:32:05,260 --> 00:32:07,360
You volunteered the information.

612
00:32:09,910 --> 00:32:12,980
Anyway, let's pretend we don't know each other,

613
00:32:12,980 --> 00:32:14,220
even if we bump into each other.

614
00:32:14,220 --> 00:32:15,640
Just like we've been doing,

615
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:19,220
let's pretend we don't know each other. Okay?

616
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,800
No way in hell I'm eating the soy bean stew...

617
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,740
Don't pick them up.

618
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:34,900
Leave it. I don't want your help-

619
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:38,000
I have no intention of helping you, either.

620
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,340
You told me to pretend we don't know each other.

621
00:32:50,950 --> 00:32:53,390
Whatever. Forget it.

622
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:55,510
I erased you from my life, anyway.

623
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:57,470
You're out.

624
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:31,040
Doctor, Patient Kim Young Im is done
with physical therapy.

625
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:33,520
- I'll take her to the consultation room.
- Okay.

626
00:33:35,730 --> 00:33:36,930
How's your shoulder?

627
00:33:36,930 --> 00:33:38,470
How could she be okay?

628
00:33:38,470 --> 00:33:40,200
I'm sure she's rotting inside.

629
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:42,960
All she has to boast about is her two daughters.

630
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,290
But the first daughter got divorced

631
00:33:44,290 --> 00:33:45,470
and the second one called off the wedding.

632
00:33:45,470 --> 00:33:49,050
Right? Who knew Geum Ju would turn out like that.

633
00:33:49,050 --> 00:33:51,240
I'm sure she's mortified.

634
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:54,040
It's wild that she broke it off for a reason

635
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,500
no other than alcohol.

636
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:58,610
That's why she lied, which is so unlike her.

637
00:33:58,610 --> 00:34:01,260
You happy? You sound giddy.

638
00:34:01,260 --> 00:34:04,400
Now that she must understand what it means

639
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:07,380
to rot inside because of your children,

640
00:34:07,380 --> 00:34:10,920
I feel like the ribs I ate last month are
finally getting digested.

641
00:34:19,790 --> 00:34:21,220
[Bochun's Treasure!
Bochun's Pride! Hosu Rice Wine!]

642
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:26,810
This darn, good-for-nothing booze.

643
00:34:29,460 --> 00:34:31,030
Try this, too.

644
00:34:31,820 --> 00:34:33,310
I can't eat anymore.

645
00:34:33,310 --> 00:34:34,610
I'm full.

646
00:34:34,610 --> 00:34:37,150
Really? Then, go brush your teeth.

647
00:34:37,150 --> 00:34:39,050
<i>Okay!</i>

648
00:34:39,050 --> 00:34:40,190
Geum Ju, eat up.

649
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:41,720
Dad, I'm also done.

650
00:34:41,720 --> 00:34:43,460
Why? Eat more.

651
00:34:43,460 --> 00:34:44,840
Are you feeling anxious?

652
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:47,350
It's okay. The rumor will dissipate soon.

653
00:34:47,350 --> 00:34:49,000
It's not that...

654
00:34:51,260 --> 00:34:52,580
It's too fatty.

655
00:34:52,580 --> 00:34:56,830
Same here. A glass of beer
would go great with this.

656
00:34:56,830 --> 00:34:58,230
No.

657
00:34:58,230 --> 00:35:00,720
Pork belly pairs best with soju.

658
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:02,310
Look.

659
00:35:14,030 --> 00:35:16,870
Gosh, Dad.

660
00:35:16,870 --> 00:35:19,920
Pork belly is best with a cold beer.

661
00:35:28,670 --> 00:35:30,600
You're both wrong.

662
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:33,430
Pork belly is best with a soju and beer mix.

663
00:35:33,430 --> 00:35:35,780
Shake the soju.

664
00:35:38,910 --> 00:35:41,610
Three parts of soju

665
00:35:41,610 --> 00:35:44,160
and seven parts of beer. This is a smooth one.

666
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:47,300
It's really smooth. Really smooth.

667
00:35:50,260 --> 00:35:52,270
- Geum Ju.
- This is perfect.

668
00:35:52,270 --> 00:35:55,090
- Geum Ju?
- So perfect. I thought...

669
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:57,310
What?

670
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:00,600
Oh, the tornado.

671
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:02,480
I forgot about the tornado.

672
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:05,170
I'm going, going, going...

673
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:11,170
One shot.

674
00:36:37,660 --> 00:36:39,970
Why take away their food?

675
00:36:44,670 --> 00:36:47,230
You make me want to drink more, Mom!

676
00:36:49,130 --> 00:36:52,380
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

677
00:36:55,710 --> 00:36:58,060
The drinks taste so good.

678
00:36:58,060 --> 00:36:59,870
So delicious.

679
00:36:59,870 --> 00:37:02,230
I'll cook more meat later.

680
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:12,860
<i>Oh, really?</i>

681
00:37:16,050 --> 00:37:18,270
<i>Let's cheers to that.</i>

682
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:56,840
What are you doing so late at night?

683
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:59,970
I can't go to sleep. Just can't sleep.

684
00:38:03,370 --> 00:38:05,040
You have scissors here.

685
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:07,390
Just use the scissors.

686
00:38:07,390 --> 00:38:09,160
Why are you using your teeth? Here.

687
00:38:09,160 --> 00:38:12,070
Because I can't tear you apart with my teeth.

688
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:18,550
This is too much.

689
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:20,210
Why did you drag me down here?

690
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,620
How dare you yell at me?

691
00:38:21,620 --> 00:38:23,420
Stop grilling me.

692
00:38:23,420 --> 00:38:25,470
I'm human, too. I get hurt, too.

693
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:27,200
Get hurt?

694
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:29,460
You do whatever you want
with no regard for anyone else.

695
00:38:29,460 --> 00:38:31,140
Get hurt?

696
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,070
Do whatever I want?

697
00:38:34,070 --> 00:38:35,960
- Me?
- You don't?

698
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,890
Think about Ju Yeop, whom you hurt.

699
00:38:38,890 --> 00:38:41,980
Don't you feel bad? At all?

700
00:38:44,830 --> 00:38:48,810
No. I don't feel bad at all.

701
00:38:48,810 --> 00:38:50,990
Not even a little.

702
00:38:50,990 --> 00:38:52,620
That bitch...

703
00:38:53,390 --> 00:38:57,220
Gosh, I raised her wrong.

704
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:12,480
Feel bad? Bullshit.

705
00:39:13,340 --> 00:39:15,440
We fixed the problem.

706
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:17,100
The sensor data is back to normal.

707
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:18,610
As expected.

708
00:39:18,610 --> 00:39:21,320
We couldn't have resolved it if it weren't for you.

709
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:24,060
Oh, right, today's your last day
before vacation, right?

710
00:39:24,060 --> 00:39:26,880
- Yes.
- Want to get a drink?

711
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:29,800
I'm not sure...

712
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:35,320
Let's do drinks another time.

713
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:37,580
I'll go home from here.

714
00:39:37,580 --> 00:39:40,350
<i>I'll help you process the payment.</i>

715
00:39:43,570 --> 00:39:46,260
[Pregnancy Test]

716
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:48,550
<i>5,500 won.</i>

717
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:06,970
Don't worry.

718
00:40:06,970 --> 00:40:09,850
I've been meaning to break off the engagement.

719
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:15,800
No, I'll just break up with her today.

720
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:18,430
- Really?
- Yes, of course.

721
00:40:18,430 --> 00:40:20,250
So, don't cry.

722
00:40:20,250 --> 00:40:22,730
Better not scare the baby in your tummy.

723
00:40:22,730 --> 00:40:24,210
Okay?

724
00:40:24,210 --> 00:40:25,850
Don't cry.

725
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,410
[Ju Yeop]

726
00:40:56,410 --> 00:41:00,180
- Why aren't you picking up?
- He's in the way of our drinks.

727
00:41:00,180 --> 00:41:02,680
All right. Persevere. Endure.

728
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:04,710
<i>Bottoms up!</i>

729
00:41:08,170 --> 00:41:10,210
Alcohol or me. Which do you choose?

730
00:41:12,930 --> 00:41:14,450
Alcohol.

731
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:24,820
Let's forget about getting married.

732
00:41:24,820 --> 00:41:27,740
Han Geum Ju, what are you talking about?

733
00:41:27,740 --> 00:41:29,570
Let me set this straight.

734
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,120
I broke off this engagement.

735
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:33,700
I broke up with you.

736
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:35,300
Because you're...

737
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:39,350
worse than booze to me, you bastard.

738
00:42:22,230 --> 00:42:24,040
Where did you go so early in the morning?

739
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:26,290
I didn't want to be home.

740
00:42:26,290 --> 00:42:28,660
Glad to hear that. Follow me.

741
00:42:28,660 --> 00:42:30,540
What is this? Where are we going?

742
00:42:30,540 --> 00:42:32,120
Shut your mouth and follow me.

743
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:33,770
Wait. Mom!

744
00:42:33,770 --> 00:42:35,510
<i>Mom!</i>

745
00:42:39,450 --> 00:42:42,070
Where are we going?

746
00:42:43,210 --> 00:42:45,150
Mom! Mom?

747
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:46,990
Mom, Mom, Mom...

748
00:42:48,090 --> 00:42:50,290
Do you want to go on a date with me?

749
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:54,010
Gosh, are we burying something?

750
00:42:54,010 --> 00:42:55,460
I don't want to go.

751
00:42:55,460 --> 00:42:56,890
I'm so tired.

752
00:42:56,890 --> 00:42:58,270
I'm not going.

753
00:42:58,270 --> 00:43:00,730
You won't even tell me where we're going.

754
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,260
Gosh, seriously...

755
00:43:05,260 --> 00:43:07,990
This is perfect weather to get buried alive.

756
00:43:09,180 --> 00:43:11,760
How did she come up with this?

757
00:43:13,210 --> 00:43:16,820
She wants me to collect mountain spring water?

758
00:43:16,820 --> 00:43:21,620
She sure comes up with all kinds
of methods of torture.

759
00:43:21,620 --> 00:43:23,870
Yes, Monk.

760
00:43:23,870 --> 00:43:26,600
I'd like to contribute a roof tile
in the name of Han Geum Ju.

761
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,350
I will offer 500,000...

762
00:43:29,300 --> 00:43:32,530
No, I'll wire over one million won.

763
00:43:32,530 --> 00:43:34,460
- One million won?
- Nongmin Bank...

764
00:43:34,460 --> 00:43:37,430
- 3319...
- 3319...

765
00:43:37,430 --> 00:43:38,610
What are you doing right now?

766
00:43:38,610 --> 00:43:39,880
Can't you tell?

767
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:41,900
I'm praying to Buddha so that

768
00:43:41,900 --> 00:43:45,470
you can quit drinking once and for all.

769
00:43:45,470 --> 00:43:47,210
Excuse me.

770
00:43:47,210 --> 00:43:48,560
Come here.

771
00:43:48,560 --> 00:43:50,120
Stop it. Why are you doing this?

772
00:43:50,120 --> 00:43:51,330
Why do you think?

773
00:43:51,330 --> 00:43:53,140
I'm trying to enlist Buddha's help.

774
00:43:53,140 --> 00:43:55,370
I don't need to quit drinking!

775
00:43:55,370 --> 00:43:57,350
You still don't get it, do you?

776
00:43:57,350 --> 00:43:58,540
Step aside.

777
00:43:58,540 --> 00:44:01,060
Monk, I will wire the money right away.

778
00:44:01,060 --> 00:44:02,460
Oh, my gosh. Hey!

779
00:44:02,460 --> 00:44:03,550
Hey!

780
00:44:03,550 --> 00:44:05,420
Hey! Hey!

781
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:10,730
Han Geum Ju, just wait till I catch you!

782
00:44:10,730 --> 00:44:13,030
Hey! Stop!

783
00:44:13,030 --> 00:44:14,220
You're done the moment I catch you.

784
00:44:14,220 --> 00:44:15,730
That girl...

785
00:44:15,730 --> 00:44:17,000
Hey!

786
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:19,230
Stop right there!

787
00:44:19,230 --> 00:44:20,570
The moment I catch you...

788
00:44:20,570 --> 00:44:22,050
Hey!

789
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:35,930
Hey! Geum Ju!

790
00:44:35,930 --> 00:44:38,010
Aigoo!

791
00:44:38,010 --> 00:44:39,610
Geum Ju!

792
00:44:40,570 --> 00:44:42,460
Geum Ju!

793
00:44:42,460 --> 00:44:46,200
I'm telling you, I'm not quitting booze.

794
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:49,700
I'm not quitting. So, give up.

795
00:44:49,700 --> 00:44:52,790
Hey. Hey!

796
00:44:58,660 --> 00:45:00,320
Seriously...

797
00:45:00,320 --> 00:45:02,060
Are you okay?

798
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:08,200
Where did you come from?

799
00:45:09,510 --> 00:45:11,490
Seriously...

800
00:45:12,610 --> 00:45:15,290
- Ma'am.
- Thank you.

